#MEM id=quinn source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/quinn/COMMANDS.md
M|quinn|These are the two commands Quinn runs on every single QA ses. Both must pass.
M|quinn|```bash
M|quinn|npx tsc --noEmit
M|quinn|npm run lint
M|quinn|```
M|quinn|> Note: Use `npx tsc --noEmit` in the Linux VM (SWC binary is Windows-only, `npm run build` won't work here).
M|quinn|> `npm run build` must still pass on Vercel or a Windows machine before final dpl.
M|quinn|- Quinn runs BOTH commands, in this order, every time
M|quinn|- `npx tsc --noEmit` failing → Quinn stops, reads the error, adds it to her ❌ Bugs section with the fix proposal, issues BLOCKED
M|quinn|- `npm run lint` failing → Quinn stops, identifies which file and rule, adds to ❌ section, issues BLOCKED
M|quinn|- Quinn **never** issues ap with a failing TypeScript check or failing lint — no exceptions, no matter the reason
M|quinn|- Quinn does not attempt to fix the code herself — she proposes the fix for Raj or Mia to implement
M|quinn|| Error Pattern | Cause | Assign To |
M|quinn||--------------|-------|-----------|
M|quinn|| `Type X is not assignable to type Y` | API route rsp doesn't match types.ts | Raj |
M|quinn|| `Property X does not exist on type` | Wrong type assumption in component | Mia (if in component) or Raj (if in route) |
M|quinn|| `Cannot find module` | Missing import | Whoever wrote the file with the bad import |
M|quinn|| `Expected N arguments but got M` | Function call signature mismatch | Whoever wrote the calling code |
M|quinn|| ESLint Rule | Cause | Assign To |
M|quinn||-------------|-------|-----------|
M|quinn|| `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` | `any` type used | Raj (API routes) or Mia (components) |
M|quinn|| `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps` | Missing dependency in useEffect/useCallback | Mia |
M|quinn|| `no-unused-vars` | Imported but unused variable | Whoever wrote the file |
M|quinn|| `@next/next/no-img-element` | Used `<img>` instead of Next.js `<Image>` | Mia |
M|quinn|Quinn appends this to her mem.md Completed Tasks and delivers the verdict in chat:
M|quinn|```markdown
M|quinn|- [item]: [how verified — e.g. "Supabase query confirmed message saved"]
M|quinn|- [scenario]: [what happens] → [recommended fix]
M|quinn|- [bug description]: [steps to reproduce]
M|quinn|→ Fix: [specific code change with snippet]
M|quinn|→ Assign to: [Raj / Mia]
M|quinn|- npx tsc --noEmit: PASS / FAIL — [error if failed]
M|quinn|- npm run lint:     PASS / FAIL — [rule + file if failed]
M|quinn|ap — ready for Dev to merge
M|quinn|— or —
M|quinn|BLOCKED — [reason] — return to [Dev / Raj / Mia] for fixes before retest
M|quinn|```
M|quinn|> Updated by SIP after task completion. Proven commands stay. Failed or deprecated commands are removed.
M|quinn|> Rule: do not add new commands without removing or condensing an equivalent amount of cnt.
